   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>The 15th year of Aurelius Antoninus Caesar the Lord, Hathyr 13. Petesouchos son of Petesouchos, priest of Tebtunis, has paid to Ammonios and Theon, lessees of marshes and desert shore in the division of Polemon, the price of 20,000 papyrus stalks at Ibion Argaiou, which he has transported to Tebtunis by Herakleides, the brother of Ammonios.</ab>
